✅ 1. GET Method
Data passed via URL (?key=value)

Example:

php
Copy
Edit
<a href="page2.php?name=John">Go</a>
// page2.php: $_GET['name']

✅ 2. POST Method
Data sent via HTML form (not visible in URL)

Example:

html
Copy
Edit
<form method="POST" action="page2.php">
  <input name="name">
  <input type="submit">
</form>
// page2.php: $_POST['name']

✅3. SESSION
Stores data on the server

Example:

php
Copy
Edit
session_start();
$_SESSION['user'] = 'Alice'; // Set
echo $_SESSION['user'];      // Get

✅ 4. COOKIE
Stores data in the browser

Example:

php
Copy
Edit
setcookie("user", "Tom", time()+3600);  // Set
echo $_COOKIE['user'];                 // G
